<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aaldiana D'Ozz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Saturday I was killing aviaks then raptors in Timorous and got 48.  Woot!  <P>Mid day I got an invite to go to Hate so heck, why not.  That raid was fairly uneventful.  Had just gotten to the top of the loot list when we called it a night  (figures huh?).  During the night I again had a couple of chances to get that 'you're not 49 so you're not good enough' frustration...including one point where I got rezzed just in time to hear "You shouldnt have rezzed her yet, she cant help."<P>*sigh*<P>Sunday went back to Hate and this time it was quite different as I was the cleric for the pull group.  (And yes a few people commented on why was the 48 cleric in the pull group..to which my entire group replied "because we want her". Plus one other cleric pointed out "Pre Kunark having a 48 cleric was always good enough, why isn't it now?"  Made me feel good  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">) Died 7 times throughout the night, regaining 48 each time through rezzes, but had an absolute blast.  It was fun to know what was happening every step of the way and learning to time the heals and buffs on our FD puller so as not to aggro anything.  Got the chance to fight Maestro for the first time also.  Unfortunately that was a failed attempt, but still I had fun anyway.  <P>And as is true to my luck...:<BR>It will take 5 more seconds to prepare your camp.<BR>YOU have been slain by Maestro of Rancor!<P>Had to laugh at that one.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>Yesterday I was playing my SK twink and was close to logging for the night when I get a tell from a friend: "Could you PLEASE come rez Fear?  We had a major wipeout and no clerics."<P>ACK!<P>So, I logged on Aal, got a port over to Feerrott and ran into Fear.  I find a hill full of bodies and a couple of people milling about.  I couldn't resist doing a quick OOC  "Did someone call for a medic?"   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I then ask if there are any enchanters to rez first.  The answer was "No, we didnt have any enchanters."  Double ack!  So instead I first rezzed the single bard and the necros.  Followed by the lone pally since he could cover buffs.  So there I am grouped with a bard and paladin and getting mana dumped on by 2 necros.  I actually managed to do all 20 rezzes in a fairly short period of time. <P>Unfortunately a couple of wandering mobs decided that a camp full of newly rezzed people would be nice for lunch and I ended up having to rerez quite a few of the people.  And in a bit of irony, my bard and pally managed to get us the xp for both mobs.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  I ended up being there about an hour and a half doing rezzes, rerezzing, buffing people... <P>Before I left I was overwhelmed by the thanks of the people there (not to mention the amount of begging to stay!).  Not a single person made any comment about it being only a 39 rez.<P>The whole Fear experience reaffirmed for me why I love being a cleric.  <P>I needed that   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR><P>------------------<BR><B>Aaldiana D'0zz</B><BR>Lvl 47 Cleric of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR>Guild Leader of <I><A HREF="http://mav.nu/hb" TARGET=_blank>HonorBound</A></I><BR>-------------------<BR>"Before you criticize someone, always walk a mile in their shoes first. That way, when you do criticize them, you're a mile away... plus you have their shoes!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hrmm<P>Both congratz and sorry to hear that.<P>It's frustrating to go and help out on an invite only to get slapped in the face with that bit about should have waited to res her since she can't help.  I feel that each and every person can contribute.  <P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>52nd Dwarven Vicar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SeaOfHoles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I got my 1st "random" invite to Fear this weekend.  Too bad I can't go yet, as I am only level 45.<P>BTW, at what level would you suggest going to Fear/Hate?  Minimum of 47?  If I happened to die enough to put me in jeopardy of losing level 46, I am assuming I would be advised to call it a night.<P>------------------<BR><B>Murrachan Moorsfang</B>(45th Rank Dwarven Priest)<BR><B>Briathrachan Moorsfang</B>(40th Rank Halfling Warrior)<BR>Mist Riders<BR>Mithaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SeaofHoles-<P>My opinion is thus:<P>On 100% respawn-only farms of fear and hate, feel free to go at 47 if they will have you. <P>On a fear/hate break, avoid, avoid, avoid. Try again at 49/50.<P>------------------<BR>Alliliel Archfalcon<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Consul of Initiates<BR>The Sisters of Virtue<BR>Tunare Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SeaOfHoles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ya.  I think that is good advice.  Going on easier "farm" expeditions will allow me to gauge the strength and damage potential of the MOBS, so I am ready at some point for a potential break in.<P>------------------<BR><B>Murrachan Moorsfang</B>(45th Rank Dwarven Priest)<BR><B>Briathrachan Moorsfang</B>(40th Rank Halfling Warrior)<BR>Mist Riders<BR>Mithaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">zagarith</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">let see my first hate raid was 48<BR>and yes it so SO annoying hehe, all the other clerics doing ressing and me sitting on my hands :-)<P>as stated if breaking 49+ with a buffer simply as people NEED that 49 res for moral, don't ask me, they just feel better with one.<P>and CHANGE YOUR SIG IT SAYS 47 STILL  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zellidon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It isn't very unsafe to go to Hate at 47 you won't lose much if any. But fear I'd wait til 60 that place is SOOOO buggy now I'm not gonna step foot in there for a LONG time...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fear is a strange place due to the experience or lack there of, of your puller.  If you have a really good puller and makes sure you don't agro CT, you should be fine.  But if you don't do a good job pulling and CT gets agroed, you are going to have problems.<P>Definitely wait till you have a decent amount of padding in 47 to do anything.  I went on my first hate run when I was 47.  Granted if things go bad you will be asked to help with healing and buffing, but generally you won't do much of the ressing unless they are in a crunch and needed.  If you are going and the planes have been already broke, I think like others have stated, you should be fine to go at 47.<P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>52nd Dwarven Vicar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm just starting 44 but...<P>From what I know if you get a 49 res every time then all you need is to be halfway through 46 to keep from losing your level (I pay attention to our guild boards about it  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">).<P>As for the "she can't help" comment, it seems that Kunark has changed a great many attitudes. I've even heard of level 50 clerics being called useless because they didn't have Remedy or Heroism. Is it just me or have some of the 51+ people developed serious attitude problems? /sigh<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Cleric of Prexus<BR>Proud member of The Steel Wind<BR>Cazic Thule Server<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aaldiana D'Ozz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey, zagarith...this better?<P>  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR><B>Aaldiana D'0zz</B><BR>Lvl <font size=6 color=red><blink><B>48</B></blink></font> Cleric of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR>Guild Leader of <I><A HREF="http://mav.nu/hb" TARGET=_blank>HonorBound</A></I><BR>-------------------<BR>"Before you criticize someone, always walk a mile in their shoes first. That way, when you do criticize them, you're a mile away... plus you have their shoes!"<p>[This message has been edited by Aaldiana D'Ozz (edited 05-31-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">WOW<P>Hard to miss that one - hehe<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>53rd Dwarven Vicar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mlar D'Kath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would not advise doing a fear-break until well into 49 at the earliest unless there are plenty of other 49+ Clerics.The reason is that usually the clerics will bind in-zone and thus have a high risk of having multiple naked corpses,which will then decay too fast to be ressed.<P>Aaldiana,<BR>Even without 49 rez there is a lot a cleric can do during rezing.<BR>-Heal people as they are ressed<BR>-Heal Necros who are liching and mana-dumping<BR>-Heal the rezzing cleric as they chain-use modulating rods<P>Of course i bet they would have apologised damn fast if the camp got overrun and you where the only cleric able to camp out.<P><BR>Mlar D'Kath<BR>Priest of Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
